@startuml Dispute_Resolution_States

' ============================================
' STATE DIAGRAM: Dispute Resolution Lifecycle
' Bug Bounty and Its Simulation Platform
' ============================================

title Dispute Resolution State Transitions

[*] --> Initiated : Organization disputes report

Initiated --> Evidence_Collection : Dispute created
Evidence_Collection --> Researcher_Response : Researcher submits response
Researcher_Response --> Organization_Counter : Org provides counter-arguments
Organization_Counter --> Under_Mediation : All evidence collected

Under_Mediation --> Triage_Review : Triage analyst reviews
Triage_Review --> Decision_Made : Clear resolution found
Triage_Review --> Escalated : Complex case, escalate to admin

Decision_Made --> Resolved_Favor_Researcher : Decision: Favor researcher
Decision_Made --> Resolved_Favor_Organization : Decision: Favor organization

Resolved_Favor_Researcher --> Closed : Restore original assessment
Resolved_Favor_Organization --> Researcher_Appeal : Researcher can appeal
Resolved_Favor_Organization --> Closed : Researcher accepts

Researcher_Appeal --> Escalated : Appeal to admin

Escalated --> Admin_Review : Admin investigates
Admin_Review --> Expert_Consultation : Need external opinion
Expert_Consultation --> Admin_Review : Expert provides input
Admin_Review --> Final_Decision : Admin makes final decision

Final_Decision --> Closed : Dispute resolved

Closed --> [*]

note right of Evidence_Collection
  Evidence phase:
  - Researcher response (3 days)
  - Organization counter (3 days)
  - Additional clarifications
end note

note right of Triage_Review
  Triage analyst:
  - Re-evaluates vulnerability
  - Tests reproduction steps
  - Reviews both arguments
  - Makes recommendation
end note

note right of Escalated
  Escalation criteria:
  - High-value disputes (>$5000)
  - Complex technical issues
  - Conflicting evidence
  - Policy interpretation needed
end note

note right of Final_Decision
  Admin decision is final
  - No further appeals
  - Binding on both parties
  - Logged for transparency
end note

@enduml
